## Severity
Critical
## Dimension
complexity
## Location
src/main.rs:1056-3900 (cmd_chat body)
## Violation
`cmd_chat` exceeds 2800 lines in a single function. Cyclomatic complexity is well past the framework threshold (V(G) > 15) — the streaming SSE branch alone is roughly 600 lines of nested match/if/while at depth 6+. Three provider paths (Anthropic streaming, Google non-streaming, OpenAI-compat streaming) duplicate substantial tool-execution scaffolding (permission gates, audit logging, plan-mode checks, auto-learn calls) at lines 1974-2126 and 2680-2820.

This is a textbook Big Ball of Mud / God Function. SRP, OCP, and KISS are all violated. The duplicate tool-execution scaffolding means a security-relevant change (e.g., adding a new gate) must be applied 3 times correctly.

A snippet showing the duplication of the permission-gate-then-execute sequence between Gemini path (line 1999-2058) and Anthropic path (line 2701-2752):

```rust
// Gemini path
let tool_args_val: serde_json::Value = serde_json::from_str(&tool_call.function.arguments)
    .unwrap_or_else(|e| { tracing::warn!("Malformed tool arguments for '{}': {}", tool_call.function.name, e); serde_json::Value::Object(serde_json::Map::default()) });
match check_tool_permission_interactive(&tool_call.function.name, &tool_args_val, dangerously_skip_permissions, &mut always_allowed_tools) { ... }
// ... then identical execute_tool_with_memory call
```

vs.

```rust
// Anthropic path (essentially the same)
let tool_args_val2: serde_json::Value = serde_json::from_str(&tool_call.function.arguments)
    .unwrap_or_else(|e| { tracing::warn!("Malformed tool arguments for '{}': {}", tool_call.function.name, e); serde_json::Value::Object(serde_json::Map::default()) });
match check_tool_permission_interactive(&tool_call.function.name, &tool_args_val2, dangerously_skip_permissions, &mut always_allowed_tools) { ... }
```

## Mandated refactor
Extract the per-turn body into structured pieces and consolidate the duplicated tool-execution scaffolding:
1. Hoist a `ToolExecutionContext` struct carrying `permission_mgr`, `audit_logger`, `auto_learner`, `always_allowed_tools` etc. plus a single `execute_one_tool(ctx, tool_call) -> Result<ToolResult>` async helper.
2. Replace the three provider streaming branches with implementations of an existing `ProviderAdapter`-style trait that returns a uniform stream of `ToolCallBatch | TextChunk | Done` events. The provider-specific JSON shape stays in providers.rs; cmd_chat stops knowing about Anthropic vs Gemini vs OpenAI.
3. Move the turn loop body out of `cmd_chat` into a `run_one_chat_turn` async fn so the surface area of the REPL outer loop is tractable.

